		<body xml:lang="it">
			<pb n="LL1.16.1r" xml:id="LL1.16_fol_1r" facs="data/test-img/LL1.16/LL1-16_0001.dzi"/>
			<!-- Fronte-recto -->
			<div n="o_01" type="opener" part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
				<dateline n="ab_01">
					<s n="s_01" type="sentence" part="N">
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_01" n="1" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_01"/>
						<date when="1834-06-26" instant="false">Juin 26</date>:
						<address>
							<placeName ref="#Put">Puteau - </placeName>
							<street>N:° 19 bis rampe</street>
							<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_02" n="2" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_02"/>
							<placeName ref="#NSS"><hi rend="underline align(right)">de Neuilly</hi></placeName>
						</address>
					</s>
				</dateline>
			</div>
			<div type="letter-body" part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
				<salute n="ab_02">
					<s n="s_02" type="sentence" part="N">
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_03" n="3" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_03"/>
						Mio caro
							<persName ref="#PepoliCarlo">Carluccio</persName>
							<ptr target="#LL1.16_note1"/><note resp="#EC" xml:id="LL1.16_note1" anchored="true">
						<p part="N">
							Bellini si riferiva al conte Carlo Pepoli, che aveva predisposto il libretto dei <hi rend="italic">Puritani.</hi>
						</p>
					</note></s>
				</salute>
				<ab n="ab_03" rend="first_line_indented" type="parag" part="N">
					<s n="s_03" type="sentence" part="N">
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_04" n="4" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_04"/>
						Avendo steso l'intero
						<term ref="TEI-ListTerm.xml#duetto" subtype="music-term">duetto</term><note type="comment" n="T"><seg>
                [DUETTO]
            </seg><gloss xml:lang="it" target="#duetto" source="TEI-ListBibl.xml#DellaSeta2010">
							Brano per due voci sole. Sin dalle origini dell'<term subtype="music-term" ref="#opera">opera,</term> il duetto fu usato, in forme simili a quelle dell'<term subtype="music-term" ref="#aria">aria,</term> come mezzo elettivo per rappresentare il contrasto o la consonanza sentimentale tra due personaggi. Nel Settecento il duetto è presente raramente nell'<term subtype="music-term" ref="#opera_seria">opera seria,</term> dove di solito è collocato alla fine di un <term subtype="music-term" ref="#atto">atto,</term> mentre è frequente nell'<term subtype="music-term">opera buffa,</term> soprattutto per le scene di vivace confronto; il suo impiego si moltiplica dall'Ottocento nelle opere italiane, francesi e tedesche di ogni genere, in cui diviene il mezzo principale per esprimere il rapporto amoroso. Nel <term subtype="music-term">melodramma</term> prevale il modello formale codificato da <persName ref="#RossiniGioachino">Rossini</persName> [...], che può essere variato in molti modi. [...]
						</gloss><seg>
                (TEI-ListBibl.xml#DellaSeta2010)
            </seg></note>
						<ptr target="#LL1.16_note2"/><note resp="#EC" xml:id="LL1.16_note2" anchored="true">
						<p part="N">
							Bellini si riferisce al terzo numero musicale del primo atto dei <hi rend="italic">Puritani,</hi> il duetto fra Elvira e Giorgio "Sai come arde in petto mio".
						</p>
					</note>
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_05" n="5" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_05"/>
						e mancando in esso qualche
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_06" n="6" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_06"/>
						cosetta, desidererei che tu
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_07" n="7" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_07"/>
						t'incommodassi a venire à
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_08" n="8" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_08"/>
						<placeName ref="#Put">Puteau</placeName> per tutto fissare, e
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_09" n="9" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_09"/>
						nell'istesso tempo darmi la
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_10" n="10" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_10"/>
						<term ref="TEI-ListTerm.xml#sortita" subtype="music-term">sortita</term><note type="comment" n="T"><seg>
                [SORTITA]
            </seg><gloss xml:lang="it" target="#sortita" source="TEI-ListBibl.xml#DellaSeta2010">
							Nell'opera del Settecento e del primo Ottocento, aria di sortita cantata da un personaggio quando compare in scena la prima volta (e quindi al momento di "sortire" dalle quinte). Nell'Ottocento un'aria di sortita in questa posizione era detta <term subtype="music-term" rend="italic">cavatina.</term>
						</gloss><seg>
                (TEI-ListBibl.xml#DellaSeta2010)
            </seg></note> di
						<persName ref="#RubiniGiovanniBattista">Rubini,</persName>
						<ptr target="#LL1.16_note3"/><note resp="#EC" xml:id="LL1.16_note3" anchored="true">
						<p part="N">
							Bellini si riferisce alla cavatina di Arturo "Ad Arturo - A te, o cara, amor talora", che segue il Coro nel quarto numero musicale del primo atto dei <hi rend="italic">Puritani.</hi>
						</p>
					</note> se è <w part="N">termi
							<lb break="no" facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_11" n="11" rend="double-stroke" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_11"/>
							nata.</w>
					</s>
					<s n="s_04" type="sentence" part="N">
						T'aspetto in qual giorno
						<lb facs="#LL1.16_line_1r_12" n="12" xml:id="LL1.16_lb_1r_12"/>
						ed in qual'ora vorrai —
					</s>
				</ab>
			</div>
